-- Allot Drops Most in Three Weeks, Narrows Gap With U.S. Shares
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2012-06-24T10:32:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-24/allot-drops-most-in-three-weeks-narrows-gap-with-u-s-shares.html
Allot Communications Ltd. (ALLT)  dropped
the most in three weeks in  Tel Aviv , narrowing the gap with the
U.S.-traded stock of the Israeli maker of high-speed networking
equipment.  The  shares  of the Hod Hasharon, Israel-based company
dropped 4.6 percent, the biggest intraday decline since June 3,
to 104.9 shekels, or the equivalent of $26.89, at 12:46 p.m. in
Tel Aviv. The stock closed at $26.78 in New York on June 22.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
